    The imposing [Ditchley House](/Ditchley_House) in [Oxfordshire](/Oxfordshire), a quintessential country house, designed by [James Gibbs](/James_Gibbs) in 1722. Its classical lines and balanced proportions are characteristic of early Georgian grandeur.

