*   [![Sutton Lodge, Sutton, London, once used by the Prince Regent, George IV of the United Kingdom](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c5/Sutton_Lodge_2015.JPG/120px-Sutton_Lodge_2015.JPG)](/File:Sutton_Lodge_2015.JPG)
    Sutton Lodge in [Sutton, London](/Sutton,_London), a distinguished residence that once served as an abode for the Prince Regent, later [George IV of the United Kingdom](/George_IV_of_the_United_Kingdom), reflecting the domestic elegance of the period.

*   [![Georgian period townhouses in Pery Square, Newtown Pery, Limerick, Ireland, after 1769](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d9/Pery_Square_Limerick.jpg/120px-Pery_Square_Limerick.jpg)](/File:Pery_Square_Limerick.jpg)
    A splendid row of Georgian period townhouses in Pery Square, part of [Newtown Pery, Limerick](/Newtown_Pery,_Limerick), [Ireland](/Ireland), constructed after 1769, showcasing the urban residential aesthetic.

