*   [![Western side of Bryanston Square, London, with its gardens. 1810–15](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Bryanston_Square_West_Side.jpg/120px-Bryanston_Square_West_Side.jpg)](/File:Bryanston_Square_West_Side.jpg)
    The western side of [Bryanston Square](/Bryanston_Square), [London](/London), with its meticulously maintained gardens, constructed between 1810 and 1815, epitomizing the late Georgian urban square development.

